  "text": "Note that although the bound for mellowmax under the entropy-regularized MDP framework was shown in [CITATION_1] to have a better scalar term log(m) instead of (m − 1), its convergence rate is linear w.r.t. τ . In contrast, our softmax Bellman operator result has an exponential rate, as shown in Part (II). The error bound in the sparse Bellman operator [CITATION_2] improves upon log(m), but is still linear w.r.t. τ . We further empirically illustrate the faster convergence for the softmax Bellman operator in Figure 2 of Section 3.4.",
